    },
    "44290976": {
      "title": "Oxidative damage to human plasma proteins by ozone",
      "abstract": "Exposure of human plasma to ozone produces oxidative protein damage, measured as protein carbonyl formation. Isolated human albumin or creatine phosphokinase are oxidized much faster than are total proteins. Consideration must be given to proteins as targets of oxidative injury by ozone in vivo."
    }
